dle Ages."]},{"name":"Sybille","meanings":["From Greek.  See  <b>Sybil</b> ."]},{"name":"Sibella","meanings":["From the name (Greek <i>Sibylla</i> or <i>Sybilla</i>, with confusion over the vowels from an early period) of a class of ancient prophetesses inspired by Apollo. According to medieval theology, they were pagans denied the knowledge of Christ but blessed by God with some insight into things to come and accordingly admitted to heaven. It was thus regarded as a respectable name to be borne by Christians. This name was introduced to England by the Normans and enjoyed considerable popularity in the Middle Ages."]}]}],"lifeSummary":"Sybil was born about 1200, in England, United Kingdom. She had at least 1 son with William De Gardenis Of Langley."},"et":{"ABT 1200–":"umbes 1200–Surnud","1203–1264":"1203–1264","1222–1289":"1222–1289","1200–Female":"1200–Surnud","1203":"1203","1289":"1289","ABT 1200":"umbes 1200","1222":"1222","1200":"1200","1264":"1264","Langeley, Shropshire, England":"Shropshire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","England":"Inglismaa, United Kingdom"},"fi":{"ABT 1200–":"noin 1200–Kuollut","1203–1264":"1203–1264","1222–1289":"1222–1289","1200–Female":"1200–Kuollut","1203":"1203","1289":"1289","ABT 1200":"noin 1200","1222":"1222","1200":"1200","1264":"1264","Langeley, Shropshire, England":"Shropshire, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta","England":"Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta"},"fr":{"ABT 1200–":"environ 1200–Décédée","1203–1264":"1203–1264","1222–1289":"1222–1289","1200–Female":"1200–Décédée","1203":"1203","1289":"1289","ABT 1200":"environ 1200","1222":"1222","1200":"1200","1264":"1264","Langeley, Shropshire, England":"Shropshire, Angleterre, Royaume-Uni","England":"Angleterre, Royaume-Uni","lifeSummary":"Sybil est née environ 1200, à Angleterre, Royaume-Uni. Elle a eu au moins 1 fils avec William De Gardenis Of Langley."},"de":{"ABT 1200–":"um 1200–Verstorben","1203–1264":"1203–1264","1222–1289":"1222–1289","1200–Female":"1200–Verstorben","1203":"